<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="428" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1557,2016]" lastBlockId="27.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="428" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Dark morphs of this species tend to be darker than individuals from other species in the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dantas &amp; Weckstein &amp; Bates &amp; Oliveira &amp; Catanach &amp; Aleixo" authorityYear="2021" box="[1176,1302,1882,1907]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Megascops</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="ANSP" baseAuthorityYear="2445" box="[151,282,1918,1943]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="watsonii">atricapilla-M. watsonii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
complex, except for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hekstra" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[515,596,1918,1943]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[515,596,1918,1943]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">M. ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below), from which it differs mainly in back color. In some individuals of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="ANSP" baseAuthorityYear="2445" box="[183,316,1954,1980]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="watsonii">
<emphasis box="[183,206,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[221,316,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">watsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e. g. MPEG 66635), the back is black. The darker individuals also tend to have wider and bolder underparts striping than in other species of the complex, which distinguishes them from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hekstra" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[1131,1213,1990,2015]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[1131,1213,1990,2015]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">M. ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dark morphs. However, as is usual within this genus, the tremendous individual variation in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="ANSP" baseAuthorityYear="2445" box="[1003,1138,151,176]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="watsonii">
<emphasis box="[1003,1138,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">M. watsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes any generalization about diagnostic morphological characters impossible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">
Longsong distinguishable from slower-paced longsongs of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dantas &amp; Weckstein &amp; Bates &amp; Oliveira &amp; Catanach &amp; Aleixo" authorityYear="2021" box="[860,992,223,248]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stangiae">
<emphasis box="[860,992,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">M. stangiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sclater" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1045,1129,223,248]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usta">
<emphasis box="[1045,1129,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">M. usta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and faster paced longsongs of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[182,337,259,285]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atricapilla">
<emphasis box="[182,337,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">M. atricapilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[352,422,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1132,1156]" captionTargetBox="[207,1378,200,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-20@15.[207,1380,200,1108]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Geographic variation in longsong paces (notes/s) across clades A–F in the Megascops atricapilla-M. watsonii complex. Locality codes are given as letters followed by numbers and can be found in full in the Appendix. Numbers next to locality dots represent locally measured longsong pace values. When more than one individual was sampled at a given locality, the total number of longsongs measured is given in parentheses, with reported values representing averages." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640348/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
: 
<tableCitation box="[433,527,259,285]" captionStart="TABLE 6" captionStartId="14.[151,239,1560,1584]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="TABLE 6. Mean and standard deviation values of nine “longsong” characters measured for Megascops atricapilla-M. watsonii individuals belonging to clades A‒F (see also Fig. 9)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0F660FFFCA2200FF55F9FCFCCB876C" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" tableUuid="DF0F660FFFCA2200FF55F9FCFCCB876C">Tables 6</tableCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[581,612,259,285]" captionStart="TABLE 10" captionStartId="20.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 10. Results of pairwise diagnosability tests employed among Megascops atricapilla-M. watsonii clades A‒F" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0F660FFFD0221AFF55FF73FA678188" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" tableUuid="DF0F660FFFD0221AFF55FF73FA678188">10</tableCitation>
). Shortsong faster-paced than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sclater" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[980,1065,259,284]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="usta">
<emphasis box="[980,1065,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">M. usta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dantas &amp; Weckstein &amp; Bates &amp; Oliveira &amp; Catanach &amp; Aleixo" authorityYear="2021" box="[1119,1251,259,284]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stangiae">
<emphasis box="[1119,1251,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">M. stangiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[1265,1352,259,285]" captionStart="TABLE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="TABLE 8. Mean and standard deviation values of nine “shortsong” characters measured for Megascops atricapilla-M. watsonii individuals belonging to clades A‒F." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0F660FFFD5221FFF55FF73FD8581EC" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" tableUuid="DF0F660FFFD5221FFF55FF73FD8581EC">Table 8</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
